Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26, comprehensive Xinhua News Agency foreign reporters reported: On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs notified the U.S. Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the establishment and operation license of the U.S. Consulate General in Chengdu, and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to cease all business and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious problems in Sino-US relations. China has responded to the unreasonable provocation of the United States, and it is legitimate and necessary to take countermeasures.
Andrés Borks, director of the China Studies Center of the Institute of International Studies of the University of Chile, said that the unilateral measures of the United States have destroyed the bridge of understanding between the peoples of China and the United States and caused a crisis in the relationship between the two major powers.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures of the United States and conforms to diplomatic practice.
Patricio Giusto, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Arab-Chinese Research Center, believes that the above-mentioned Chinese decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocation of the United States and is not aimed at ordinary Americans.
The United States tried to use pressure on China to cover up its ineffective response to the new crown epidemic and divert the attention of the American people.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic stance adopted by the United States has caused serious problems in Sino-US relations, and the bilateral relations are facing severe challenges.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure and conforms to diplomatic practice. It not only reflects China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also reflects the rationality and efficiency of China's diplomacy.
Francis Semwenza, a current affairs commentator in Tanzania, said that China's above decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the provocation of the United States.
If Sino-US relations are to return to normal, the United States should take the initiative to improve relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve a win-win situation with China economically and politically, and how to benefit the people of the two countries and the entire international community.
Ali Yousef, executive director of the Arab-Chinese Friendship Association Federation based in Sudan, said that the countermeasures that China was forced to take were a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the United States, in accordance with international law and the basic norms of international relations, and in accordance with diplomatic practice.
The previous request by the United States to close the Chinese Consulate General in Houston seriously violated international law and the basic norms of international relations.
It is hoped that the United States will rescind the previous relevant decisions and create necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore's "United Morning Post" published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the tight pace of the United States, although China is very reluctant to see Sino-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
