Xinhua News Agency, Guangzhou, July 26 (Reporter Mao Xin) The reporter learned from the Guangdong Maritime Police Bureau that recently, the bureau, together with the Guangzhou Customs and Public Security Department, knocked out a super-large refined oil smuggling gang, and preliminarily verified that the gang has smuggled about 120,000 tons of refined oil since 2019, with a case value of about 800 million yuan, and tax evasion of about 240 million yuan.
