"Plug up Jiangnan" to pursue the poetic "Yellow River Dream "-Chinanews.com
(China Poverty Reduction Story) "Put Jiangnan" Pursuit of Poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Agency, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuqu Yellow River Wanli Sands, waves and winds ripple from the horizon."
The Yellow River, which has aroused the feelings of countless literati, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Today, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "stuffing Jiangnan", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority, green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream."
The "Bebo Dream" of the River Qingshui Show
"The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia." The Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers. It is the "mother river" for raising one side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development and utilization of rivers and lakes are unbalanced with management and protection, and chaos such as over-standard sewage discharge, lake reclamation, and encroachment on waters have emerged, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of diverse water ecology and working hard to return the Yellow River.
Water control must start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of "standard improvement + pollution control + strict management", all sewage in industrial parks were treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants achieved level A standard discharge, and the black and smelly water bodies in urban built-up areas were basically eliminated, and the third batch of Chinese black and smelly water demonstration cities was successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake length system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake chief responsibility system in districts, cities, counties and villages, and the river and lake long patrol has become the norm.
The 64-year-old Gu Jincheng lives in a village by the Yellow River. He witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: "The previous water has a bad smell, and after rectification, the smell is gone."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is good and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk by the Yellow River with his family to feel the blue water and blue sky.
The "Wetland Dream" of Shagull Xiang Collection
Birds, green trees, stacks, clear water... the beautiful scenery of "Sand Gull Xiang Collection" written by Fan Zhongyun has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands, and swamp wetlands along the way, which play an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and water ecological balance, and have also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan Wetland covers an area of 192,000 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%, there are nearly 200 natural lakes and marsh wetlands, and there are 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks, and 8 municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. "The gull is an endangered bird. There are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which Yinchuan Wetland is home to more than 2,000."
At the same time, Ningxia established a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that except for public welfare projects, no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the protected area.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Resources Service Center, introduced that through the treatment of the source of pollution, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology, and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of the nine main yellow drains in Ningxia has now reached 100% of the first class standards. "Now the water is also clear, the fish are swimming, and the flowers are blooming."
The "Drinking Water Dream" of inclusive people's livelihood
Yinchuan City in Ningxia once had the title of "embarrassed": The only city along the Yellow River that "guarded the Yellow River for lack of water and drink."
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing a persistent shortage of water during the peak summer period. The "pain of water shortage" in the past ten years has become a painful summer experience for many high-floor residents. However, under the current situation that major water sources are at the limit of over-mining and a large area of groundwater over-mining funnel area has been formed under the urban underground, water-borne water shortage has become a problem besetting Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good way to solve the drinking water problems of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of the Yinchuan Water Affairs Bureau, introduced that in order to improve the production and water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia duly launched the urban and rural western water supply project in Yinchuan Metropolitan Area, and replaced the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially opened water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank Yellow River water."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Department will comprehensively consider the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. "In the next step, we will integrate all the scattered rural water supply points into the western water supply project, and it is expected that the integrated urban and rural water supply in the Yinchuan region will be basically achieved by the end of this year."
