Experts suggest that when you go out in summer, try to avoid high-temperature periods, and it is best not to walk or work in the hot sun around noon, because the sun is the strongest during this period and the likelihood of heatstroke is higher.
If you must go out during this period, you must do a good job of protection, such as playing a parasol, wearing a sun hat, and wearing sunglasses. If possible, it is best to apply sunscreen to prevent sunburns.
