Brazilian research shows that hydroxychloroquine is ineffective in the treatment of mild to moderate new crown pneumonia-Chinanews.com
Recently, a Brazilian study showed that hydroxychloroquine is ineffective in patients with mild new coronary pneumonia.
The study was published in the New England Journal of Medicine.
Pakistani researchers divided 667 patients from 55 hospitals across the country into three groups and conducted clinical trials; mainly compared the therapeutic effects of hydroxychloroquine alone or in combination with other antibiotics azithromycin, and analyzed whether it would help to improve the condition of mild and moderate patients with new coronary pneumonia.
The results show that hydroxychloroquine not only has no therapeutic effect, but may have traumatic side effects on organs.
This research was carried out by several authoritative hospitals in Brazil such as Hospital Israel Albert Einstein, Cardiology Hospital (HCor), Syrian Lebanese Hospital (Hospital Sírio-Libanês), etc., in conjunction with the Brazilian Clinical Research Institute (BCRI) and the Brazilian Critical Care Research Network (BRICNet).
On the 25th local time, Brazilian President Bolsonaro announced through a social platform that the fourth nucleic acid test result was negative.
During the infection, Bolsonaro has been taking hydroxychloroquine and has actively promoted it many times.
