Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 25 (Reporters Yu Junjie and Chen Aiping) The reporter learned from the State Cyberspace Administration on the 25th that the 2020 App illegal collection and use of personal information governance work was officially launched recently, focusing on issues such as the private uploading of personal information in the App backstage.
It is reported that this round of App governance is carried out by the four departments of the State Cyberspace Administration, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, the Ministry of Public Security, and the State Administration of Market Supervision.
According to reports, a special governance working group composed of four departments received more than 12,000 effective reports from netizens last year, conducted inspections on more than 2,300 apps, and adopted public exposure, interviews, and dismount penalties for 260 apps with large user sizes and prominent problems.
According to the relevant person in charge of the National Cyberspace Administration, the current number of Apps has exceeded 5 million, and the problem of illegal collection and use of personal information has not been fundamentally resolved.
In 2020, governance work will be further strengthened, and on the basis of App verification, the scope of governance will be further expanded to SDK (software development toolkit) and small programs.
It is reported that the working group will conduct special research and in-depth testing on issues such as the irregular collection and use of personal biometric information and the abuse of sensitive permissions by App, focusing on background permission abuses such as recording and photographing.
According to the circumstances of the problem and the severity of the consequences, the working group will impose penalties such as interviews, warnings, takeoffs, and fines in accordance with laws and regulations to form an effective deterrent to violations of laws and regulations.
It is understood that the working group plans to formulate and issue App Store Review and Management Guidelines for the Collection and Use of Personal Information, to guide and urge App Stores to do a good job of pre-launch review of App, and to strictly close the door.
In addition, the working group will also issue free technical tools to guide small and medium-sized enterprises to carry out self-assessment and improve the legal compliance of small and medium-sized enterprises' personal information collection and use activities.
