The landslide in Wulong Mountain in Chongqing formed a barrier lake and the local emergency transferred more than 500 people-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporters Zhou Wenchong, Ke Gaoyang) The reporter learned from the Wulong District Government of Chongqing on the 26th that the heavy rains caused landslides in the area and formed a barrier lake, and more than 500 people were urgently transferred.
Affected by the continuous rainfall, since July 22, the soil at the rear edge of the Zhongbao landslide in Zhongtai Group, LiuJing Village, Land Township, Wulong District, has cracked and a large area of sliding deformation has occurred, and the landslide has fallen into the Wujiang tributary along the Cang River.
On the 25th, a heavy rainfall weather process occurred in the local area, and the landslide further expanded, causing the village road to be interrupted and completely blocked along the Cang River, forming a barrier lake with a water level of 13 meters in front of the dam and a storage capacity of about 420,000 cubic meters.
According to on-site investigation and monitoring, the landslide has a volume of about 1.3 million cubic meters and is still in an unstable state, with sporadic rockfalls. The barrier lake has overflowed the dam, and there is a risk of embankment collapse, posing a threat to downstream power stations and field towns.
After the dangerous situation occurred, the local government organized the evacuation of residents along the river overnight, and urgently transferred the people to safety.
At present, 162 households and 520 people in the dangerous area have been evacuated, and the disposal of the barrier lake is still in progress.
