Xinhua News Agency, Kuala Lumpur, July 25 (Reporter Lin Hao) The Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) member trade ministers held a video conference on the 25th. The meeting pledged to work to reduce the impact of the new crown epidemic on the region's economy and accelerate the realization of a resilient, sustainable and inclusive regional economic recovery.
The meeting was chaired by Malaysia, the host of this year's APEC Leaders Informal Meeting.
The joint statement issued after the meeting stated that APEC member trade ministers recognize the importance of a free, open, fair, non-discriminatory, transparent and predictable trade and investment environment to promote economic recovery at this challenging time.
