News from our newspaper (Reporter Yang Zhaokui) The "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") recently released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center shows that due to the impact of the epidemic, the transaction value of my country's shared accommodation market fell by 72.1% year-on-year in the first 5 months of 2020.
However, the shared accommodation market has rebounded since March, and the market transaction volume, order volume and number of receptions have gradually recovered.
