The overall stability of employment and prices shows that the economy has a "temperature"
Economic Daily, China Economic Net Reporter Lin Yancan
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, my country coordinated efforts to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The epidemic prevention and control situation has continued to improve, the economy has steadily recovered, the performance of employment and prices that are closely related to the people's livelihood has been generally stable, and the Chinese economy has handed over a report card of economic performance with temperature.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate has increased.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of shutdown. The demand for employment by enterprises decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the production and life order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Party Central Committee adheres to the general tone of seeking progress while maintaining stability, further strengthens the macro-policy countermeasure, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of assisting enterprises to stabilize jobs and expand employment.
My country has stepped up its policies to stabilize jobs, hit the "reduction, exemption, delay, return and compensation" policy combination, phased reduction and exemption of three social insurance unit contributions, allowing deferred payment of social insurance premiums, expanding the unemployment insurance for small, medium and micro enterprises to stabilize the return of jobs, and benefiting from the training policy with workers, and giving enterprises absorption subsidies and trainee subsidies to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various employment stabilization policies, the demand for employment by enterprises has steadily rebounded, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the surveyed unemployment rate in urban areas has gradually decreased. In June, the surveyed unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Population and Employment Statistics Department of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to be effective, and the labor force who withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic in the previous period returned one after another. The urban labor participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, close to the same period last year.
Data show that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; the average weekly working hours of corporate employees reached 46.8 hours, an increase of 6.6 hours from February and a slight increase of 0.1 hours from January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January this year, the CPI rose by 5.4% year-on-year, setting a new high for many years.
Entering February, although the year-on-year increase of CPI fell slightly, it was still in the "5 range."
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, due to factors driving consumer demand before the Spring Festival, as well as factors such as the wrong month of the Spring Festival and a low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, in January and February there were delays in logistics, untimely supply of materials, and increased transportation costs of materials across the country. In addition, some citizens hoarded and rushed to buy, and the prices of some daily necessities increased significantly.
In response to the disturbance caused by the epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure smooth transportation of materials.
Under the action of a series of policy measures, the market supply of vegetables and fruits has been strongly guaranteed.
In response to the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government promulgated the policy of ensuring supply and stabilizing prices, various regions and departments quickly implemented it. The supply of pork reserves has improved significantly, the production capacity of live pigs has been restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and distribution has gradually become normal.
Since March, pork prices have continued to decline. In May, the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6%. In June, affected by factors such as the slowdown in the release of live pigs, the decrease in imports, and the rebound in group consumption demand, pork prices rose slightly.
The seasonal variation of fresh vegetable prices is obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high comparison base in the same period last year, the price of fresh fruits continued to decline year-on-year, with an average drop of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic lives of the masses are effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation remains stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, various regions have increased their efforts to ensure supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Starting in March, the CPI ring fell for four consecutive months. The year-on-year increase also fell from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the overall price level returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to remain at a moderate level, and the overall inflationary pressure is not large, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and living order under the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in major agricultural production areas such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on behaviors that disrupt market order such as hoarding and price hikes.
