Recently, with the respect of Chinese filmmakers' heroes in the fight against the epidemic, Yu Dong, chairman of Bona Pictures Group, and Liu Weiqiang, director (picture left), held talks and exchanges with academician Zhong Nanshan in Guangzhou on the filming and production of the anti-epidemic film "Chinese Doctor."
Bona Pictures hopes to pay tribute to all medical and epidemic prevention workers who are fighting on the front line of epidemic prevention and control through "Chinese Doctor"!
In 2021, the film will be released nationwide as a tribute film celebrating the 100th anniversary of the founding of the Communist Party of China.
At present, Bona Pictures is organizing the original crew of the film "Captain of China" to make the film "Chinese Doctor" under the arrangements and deployment of the Central Propaganda Department and the National Film Bureau, with the support of the Guangdong Film Bureau and the Hubei Film Bureau. This is a film that reflects the unity of the people of the country to fight the new crown pneumonia epidemic under the strong leadership of the Party Central Committee.
The film focuses on the front line of Wuhan's anti-epidemic, and will take Wuhan medical staff and provincial and municipal aid medical teams as the background of the characters. From the perspective of human nature, using unique narratives and highly impactful lens language, the panorama shows the touching story of Chinese medical staff full of dedication and sacrifice on the anti-epidemic front line.
It is understood that at the first time on the day when Wuhan was unblocked, Bona Company overcame many difficulties and dispatched a shooting team to go deep into the front line of the epidemic, face-to-face exchanges with hundreds of medical workers to understand and collect information. At present, it has interviewed academician Zhong Nanshan himself, the first person from Guangzhou to aid Wuhan, the Guangdong aid to Hubei medical team, and the white-clothed angels at the forefront of the anti-epidemic front such as Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, Wuhan Union Hospital, Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital, Wuhan Central Hospital, etc., have photographed a large number of precious first-hand video materials.
Academician Zhong Nanshan also raised expectations and hopes for the filming of the film at this symposium: "I am looking forward to it, and I hope that you will not only visit some experts who have made more public appearances, but also interview more medical staff who are working hard on the front line, they are the majority."
He said that he had seen "I and My Motherland" and "Chinese Captain" before and thought that the way to tell the big pattern story from the perspective of ordinary people is very good.
"Now some foreign friends still have some misunderstandings about China."
When talking about the dissemination of the film, academician Zhong Nanshan said that at present some people in foreign countries like to label the virus as politicized, and he hopes that the film can impress the audience from the perspective of human nature: "In addition to being shown in China, it is best to show it abroad. It is necessary to impress the audience with a true humanistic spirit in a way that both domestic and foreign audiences can understand."
Academician Zhong Nanshan also fondly recalled the film "Man to Middle Age" from the 1980s. "After so many years, what impressed me most about the film after the reform and opening up was" Man to Middle Age. "At that time, my doctors and friends abroad were crying. If" Chinese Doctor "could play such a role, it would be great."
Academician Zhong Nanshan said that if "Chinese Doctor" can resonate with foreign audiences, it will be very successful.
