Telecommunications network fraud crimes rose by 70% in the first half of the year. Summary characteristics-Chinanews.com
China News Service, July 26. According to the Supreme Inspection website, in the first half of this year, procuratorial organs across the country prosecuted a total of 58,101 fraud crimes, an increase of 35% year-on-year.
Especially among crimes that hinder the prevention and control of the epidemic, fraud crimes are frequent, and the number of prosecutors prosecuting fraud crimes accounts for 43.4% of all crimes that hinder the prevention and control of the epidemic.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance. Among the ten batches of typical cases involving epidemic prevention and control that have been released so far, there are a total of 9 cases involving fraud.
Judging from the handling of cases by procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are many names involved in fraud crimes, ranging from national macro policies to people's clothing, food and housing, including epidemic-related fraud, "medical care" fraud, "health care product" fraud, "admission agency" fraud, "routine loan" fraud, fraudulent state subsidy fraud, national asset unfreezing fraud, etc., continue to "innovate", covering education, medical care, employment, pension, social security, land acquisition and demolition, precision poverty alleviation, financial credit and other fields, which not only cause economic losses to victims, but also seriously affect economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunications network frauds break through the restrictions of national boundaries, regions and people, and have the characteristics of stakeholder, cross-border, remote, and e-payment. There are many non-specific victim groups and great harm.
For example, some set up special companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or posts, use legal online platforms to publicize and recruit, train and evaluate recruiters, and adopt corporate operation mode management, wearing a "legal cloak", which is more confusing.
Punishing and preventing crimes in accordance with the law, and promptly issuing early warnings to the public and relevant departments are the unshirkable responsibilities of procuratorial organs.
In judicial cases, procuratorial organs conscientiously perform their duties, not only insisting on maintaining a high-pressure situation against fraud crimes, but also refining various law enforcement measures in a targeted manner, and promoting social governance through the issuance of procuratorial recommendations.
The procuratorial organs strictly control the facts, evidence, procedures and application of the law in approving and prosecuting fraud cases, and take the facts as the basis and the law as the criterion, so as not to be in vain.
Especially for telecommunications network fraud crimes, pay attention to the core role of electronic data in fact determination, and strive to build an evidence chain of mutual confirmation between electronic data, verbal evidence, and documentary evidence.
For example, in response to an epidemic-related fraud case handled by the Yinzhou District Procuratorate of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province, the procuratorial organs intervened as soon as possible. From the occurrence of the case to the completion of the case, it took only 5 days, reflecting the attitude and determination to handle the case quickly and strictly and maintain the stability of the overall social situation.
In the process of reviewing arrests and reviewing prosecutions, we focused on the prosecution of missed offenders in cases, corrected the omission of 733 people by public security organs, and corrected the omission of public security organs to review and prosecute 1113 co-offenders.
In the first half of the year, procuratorial organs across the country issued 298 procuratorial recommendations for fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promoting in-depth governance.
For example, in response to the loopholes in the supervision of telecommunications companies, banks, intermediary organizations, etc., found in the handling of the case, the Guangzhou Procuratorate of Guangdong Province and the Dongguan Procuratorate promptly put forward procuratorial recommendations, urging relevant units to strengthen supervision, improve mechanisms, and promote the construction of long-term systems.
The fourth is to make every effort to recover stolen goods and recover damages.
Local procuratorial organs seize important links such as intervening in investigations to guide evidence collection, review and prosecution, urge investigative agencies to actively recover stolen money, cooperate with relevant departments to recover stolen goods, and strive to minimize the economic losses caused by fraud crimes to the people.
For example, in the case of Lin Moumou Road Loan handled by the Beijing Municipal Procuratorate, the case involved 22 properties waiting to be seized. In cases where the property may be disposed of in advance by other cases, the "Letter of Suspension of Execution" was first issued and delivered to the relevant court in a timely manner. It is recommended that the previously sealed court suspend the execution of the property involved in the case, and dispose of it uniformly after the facts of the crime are ascertained, so as to make the best efforts to recover the property involved and recover the losses of the victims.
The prosecutor reminded everyone to be very vigilant against fraud crimes, don't expect "pie in the sky", and don't be credulous when you think it's cheap, and guard your own "money bag."
