In the heat and heat, a reporter from Economic Daily-China Economic Net walked into Zhonghai Village, Yina Town, Weining County, Guizhou Province.
In the hot sun, villager Li Yuanzhong was weeding in the base. Although his face was red, he hummed a few small songs from time to time.
Weining County, where Yina Town is located, because of low latitude, high altitude, sufficient light, and large temperature difference between day and night, produces apples with high sugar content and good taste. It has a certain reputation in the surrounding area, but also because of its small size and many spots, it has not been able to sell a good price and has not been able to form an industrial scale.
Yina Town used to be a poverty-stricken township that "covered the valley with potato for spring and autumn", and the local poverty incidence rate was as high as 25.8% 10 years ago.
As the fight against poverty enters a critical period of decisive victory, it is urgent to change traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure, and increase farmers' income.
After many visits, Chen Chao, secretary of the Party Committee of Yina Town, and a group of people in the town believed that industrial development could not go the same way.
To this end, Yina Town introduced leading enterprises and planted apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Beyond Agriculture Co., Ltd. came to Yina Town from Shaanxi in 2015 to investigate, saw the local planting conditions at a glance, and began to plant apple trees there in 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees, and Li Yuanzhong and his wife murmured in their hearts: "After planting apples for so many years, I didn't see who in the village planted apples and made a fortune."
"All the apples planted are dwarfed apples, which will not make the apple trees grow too tall."
What Li Yuanzhong did not expect was that this time the apple planting adopted a new method. The irrigation pipe was laid under each apple tree, and the water and fertilizer were poured to the roots of the tree. When the fruit was harvested in autumn, the tractor drove directly into the orchard and stood to pick the fruit.
At present, the apple base has gradually entered a productive period, and the market is as expected by Hou Jianwen. Apples are not worried about selling and are loved by consumers in cities such as Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life. Although he is still planting land, he has a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family has more than 9 acres of land transferred to the apple base. In addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee, there are profit dividends after hanging the fruit. The couple usually work in the base. "One person can get 80 yuan a day, and there is work all year round."
Li Yuanzhong told reporters that last year's profit dividend earned more than 2,800 yuan, together with the land transfer fee and the couple's labor income, the family earned more than 80,000 yuan. "There is no worry about food and clothing, and a well-off life has been lived."
"At present, it has begun to bear fruit. The annual output value of 1 mu of apples exceeds 15,000 yuan, about 10 times that of corn."
Chen Chao told reporters that the whole town of Yina has currently planted 20,000 acres of apples, and there are 6,000 acres in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 households and 17,200 people, including 656 poor households and 2,952 people. The salary paid in a year is more than 6 million yuan, which truly realizes that the base is built in front of the home, and there is no need to go out for work.
Li Yuanzhong, whose waist is gradually bulging, has also begun to realize his "wish."
During the Lunar New Year this year, Li Yuanzhong bought a Land Cruiser and now drives his car to and from work every day. "There are more than a dozen acres of land in the family, so the next step is to expand the size of Apple's base and transfer it all to them, and the income will be more."
