Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect "-Chinanews.com
Membrane separation technology helps crack the "greenhouse effect"
Schematic diagram of new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology
Our reporter Shang Rui reported: Recently, the Tianjin University Atmospheric Environment and Bioenergy Team has made significant progress on the "membrane separation method to capture carbon dioxide" and has successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology, which greatly improves the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
The relevant results have been published as the cover article of the international journal "Greenhouse Gas: Science and Technology."
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem that plagues human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit responsible for the "greenhouse effect."
How to efficiently capture and use carbon dioxide emitted by humans is the focus of attention of scientists.
"Membrane separation method" is an emerging carbon dioxide capture technology. It separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials, and has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving and simple operation.
How to let the membrane material "breathe deeply" and improve the efficiency of gas separation is the bottleneck difficulty in capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation method.
The scientific research team of Tianjin University innovated ideas and explored the influence of different solvents on membrane gas separation performance through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that with N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, the carbon nanotubes in the produced membrane material are more evenly distributed and "more breathable", which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of the mixed matrix membrane prepared with this new technology is close to the current theoretical separation upper limit of such membrane materials.
"New technology provides new ideas for membrane separation to capture carbon dioxide."
Li Run, a member of the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University, said: "We hope that this technology can provide strong support for coal-fired power plants and chemical companies to process flue gas in the future, and play a major role in controlling greenhouse gas emissions."
Before volunteering, understand what is a professional level difference-Chinanews.com
2020-07-2702: 22: 36 Source: Chongqing Morning News Author: Yu Xiao Responsible Editor: Yu Xiao
Understand what is a professional grade difference before volunteering.
Every year when you report for the college entrance examination, there are students or parents who do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary filing, which affects the voluntary filing.
This year, five colleges and universities including Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued the 2020 admissions policy, eliminating the professional level difference.
What is the meaning of professional level difference, and what is the significance in voluntary filing?
There are three ways of professional distribution rules
Experts remind that before filling in a volunteer, you must read the "Admissions Regulations" of your favorite school and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the transfer ratio, professional distribution rules, etc.
Professional distribution rules mean that after colleges and universities are transferred, there are three main methods for professional admission: Major priority, score priority, and professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the "Admissions Regulations."
However, there are also some colleges and universities whose admission principle is that the total score is first, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, candidates in the admission range will be queued according to the total score. When the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score, it will be determined whether the second professional volunteer admission score line has been reached, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer, there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional level difference" means that when colleges and universities arrange candidates' majors, they determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates from different majors according to one or several points announced in the admission charter. This score is the "professional level difference."
That is, the difference between the scores of colleges and universities when admitting candidates for the first professional volunteer and non-first professional volunteer, and the grade difference between the professional volunteers, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Suppose that student Xiaoming applied for college A and scored 560 points. His professional volunteers are: Computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce. The professional admission of college A adopts the method of professional grade difference, which is divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, and 0 points.
When making professional assignments, if Xiaoming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, then Xiaoming is admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and the score of 558 points will be sorted with the candidates of the first professional volunteer to apply for "international trade" to determine whether they meet the professional admission requirements; if it is still not met, the score is subtracted by 1 point (that is, 557 points) for the admission of the third professional volunteer "automation"; if it is still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (that is, 556 points) for admission to the fourth major. If the follow-up major still fails to meet his professional volunteers, there will be no further points reduction, and so on.
Different universities have different professional level difference settings
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now eliminated the professional level difference, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year. According to the "Admissions Regulations" announced by each school, more than 20 universities have set up professional level differences this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical School, Northeast Electric Power University, Jiemei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
In these colleges and universities, the professional level difference set by each university is different.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University. Candidates whose files have been admitted to the school are admitted according to the order in which candidates fill in their professional volunteers.
And some universities have set up different professional level differences between different majors.
For example, Jiemei University, the total score of the professional volunteer level difference is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points. There is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteers, and the professional level difference between other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling in the application, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is a professional level difference, and what is the form of the level difference. While fully considering the scores, they must also reasonably analyze the school and major to be selected. If the college explicitly adopts the grade difference method for admission in the admission charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors when choosing a major to improve the chances of admission.
