The scene of the first meeting of the 3rd CIIE Exhibitors Alliance filmed in Shanghai on July 26.
Xinhua News Agency, Shanghai, July 26 (Reporter Zhou Rui) On the 26th, the 3rd Import Expo Exhibitor Alliance established a professional committee for the first time here. The first batch of special committees established include the Public Health and Epidemic Prevention Committee and the Dairy Industry Special Committee. 35 member companies have also signed a 3-year long-term exhibition cooperation memorandum, and the link role of the CIIE Exhibitor Alliance has been continuously strengthened.
At the first meeting of the 3rd CIIE Exhibitor Alliance held here on the 26th, Hyundai Korea, Dow Chemical of the United States, Shiseido of Japan, New Zealand New Zealand, Siemens of Germany, Michelin of France, and AstraZeneca of the United Kingdom signed a 3-year long-term participation memorandum of cooperation, and the revised and improved articles of association were also announced for the first time.
The scene of the establishment ceremony of the Dairy Professional Committee, filmed in Shanghai on July 26.
According to the latest constitution, the exhibition union will introduce the rotation mechanism of the lead unit to strengthen the function of the special committee.
The special committee will put forward suggestions for the analysis of industry development trends and promote the sustainable development of the industry.
At the same time, integrate the resources of the entire industrial chain of the industry, drive associated companies to participate in the exhibition, and build the CIIE into a gathering place for industry enterprises.
The establishment of a public health and epidemic prevention committee for the first time is particularly important for the current fight against the new crown pneumonia epidemic.
As the vice chairman unit of the Public Health and Epidemic Prevention Committee of the 3rd CIIE, Fu Jianping, general manager of Abbott's rapid diagnosis business in Greater China, said that in the next step, Abbott will work with more industry partners to explore new solutions and cooperation models to help China and the world fight the new crown pneumonia epidemic.
The scene of the establishment ceremony of the Public Health and Epidemic Prevention Professional Committee filmed in Shanghai on July 26.
It is reported that the 3rd CIIE established a special area for public health and epidemic prevention for the first time. As of now, nearly 50 global companies have signed up for the exhibition, with an exhibition area of more than 10,000 square meters.
During the first CIIE in 2018, the CIIE Exhibitor Alliance was established at the initiative of the exhibitors. It aims to become an exchange and cooperation platform for high-quality exhibitors, a platform for information and resource sharing among all exhibitors, and a think tank platform for promoting economic, trade and business exchanges and development between China and other countries (regions) around the world.
So far, 142 companies have joined the Exhibitor Alliance, covering 23 countries and regions around the world.
