Chengdu people gathered to watch the US consulate police prevent people from "looking too happy"
In response to the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston by the United States, China announced on Friday that it would close the U.S. Consulate General in Chengdu.
On Saturday, the badge of the U.S. Consulate was removed, and on Sunday, a dark glass car drove away from the consulate amid boos from passers-by.
On Sunday, many Chengdu people gathered in front of the US Consulate to take photos, and those who had not been there were also driven by curiosity about current events.
The AFP reporter from Chengdu Station also went to observe near the US Consulate in Chengdu and reported that there was a steady stream of curious people, and many parents took their children to take a walk to watch the consulate, take pictures of the building, or take their own photos.
The consulate was surrounded by guards, and the police "corrected" people's behavior from time to time. They seemed to not allow any unusual behavior: A woman was stopped as soon as she was about to sing a red song, and another guard confiscated a banner.
But residents of a nearby residential building successfully raised a giant Chinese flag on their balcony and shouted slogans in support of China.
The Chengdu American Consulate opened in 1985, covering all consular-related affairs of the United States in southwestern China, especially the Tibet Autonomous Region.
A reporter from the Agence France-Presse Chengdu station said that the Chinese government's response to the United States was relatively restrained: Many Chinese asked the government to close the US Consulate in Hong Kong online, but officials only said that "closing the US Consulate in Chengdu is a necessary and legal response to the unreasonable behavior of the United States."
At present, in addition to Chengdu, the United States has consulates in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan, and Hong Kong in China.
Large-scale financial media action "Walking the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" Start-Today's Highlights-Hunan Daily News Network-Huaxing Online
Hunan Daily, New Hunan Client, July 25 (Reporter from this newspaper) On July 25, the large-scale financial media operation "Walking the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" hosted by the Financial Program Center of China Central Radio and Television set out from Xuzhou, Jiangsu. Two caravans carrying a 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system were seen by guests at the scene and drove slowly out of the scene.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that "2020 is a landmark year. We will build a moderately prosperous society in an all-round way and achieve the first centenary goal. 2020 is also a year of decisive victory in the fight against poverty."
The large-scale financial media operation "Walking the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" is an important measure taken by the Finance Program Center of China Central Radio and Television to cooperate with this major theme and do a good job in poverty alleviation.
This action will go into poverty alleviation villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities across the country, dig out living poverty alleviation stories, directly attack the dramatic changes in the appearance of the village, and show how villagers can break through the dilemma of survival and development and move towards the road to wealth.
This operation will last more than 3 months.
The reporter set out from Xuzhou and took two routes, all the way to the southwest line, passing through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; the other way to the northwest line, passing through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, the journey exceeds 10,000 kilometers.
In terms of reporting format, "Walking the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" is a bold fusion.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcast through CCTV Finance Channel, CCTV Economic Voice, China Communications Broadcasting, and CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, the live TV broadcast will be completed mainly on the noon news program "World Finance" of CCTV Finance Channel (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 12: 00-13: 00), and the golden news section "Economic Information Network" of CCTV Finance Channel will open a column for poverty alleviation reports (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 20: 30-21: 30).
At the same time, the caravan will conduct a 1-hour live broadcast on the CCTV Finance client for each village it visits. By downloading CCTV Finance APP, the audience can watch the live broadcast and participate in the raffle.
In terms of technology application and studio design, "Walking the Village Live to Watch Poverty Alleviation" has the courage to make a breakthrough and pioneered the "Outfield New Media Caravan."
The car is equipped with a 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system, and uses 5G + 4K / 8K + AI technology to achieve an organic combination of online and offline, large and small screens, and television broadcasting.
Equipped with a Sanxun broadcast area, the broadcast area is converted from a container, with a length of 12 meters, a width of 2.55 meters, and a height of 3.98 meters. The box adopts a hydraulic automatic expansion structure, which can be turned up to 120 degrees.
The broadcast area can also be expanded automatically, with an external expansion platform, with an area of more than 50 square meters, which can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
At present, Dongchuan District of Kunming City is already hot in summer, and what is hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
Lu Ling, an employee of Kunming Aisford Electronics Technology Co., said, "Now, as soon as you leave your home, you enter the factory door to make money and care for your family. Thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the trade union."
Walking into the electronic component processing and poverty alleviation workshop in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a busy picture came into view.
Lu Ling, in her 40s, is a single mother who takes care of her children alone and also takes care of her elderly parents.
In her most difficult time, the Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped to come up with ideas to find a way to "send charcoal in the snow" after running.
Since 2018, Lu Ling has enjoyed housing, schooling, social security, employment and other assistance policies and assistance payments issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her child has successfully graduated and taken up employment. She herself has a job and income after participating in skills training, and she got out of poverty at the end of April.
It is reported that the special skills training project of the Dongchuan District General Organization to help combat poverty is part of the skills training work of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions.
The district always combines the characteristics of the employees in difficulties in the relocation and resettlement sites for poverty alleviation in the area, conducts in-depth investigations to understand the training needs, and determines the types of training. In the near future, it plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders, pastry chefs, etc.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Yunnan Menglian County Branch of the Agricultural Bank, wrote a sincere thank-you letter to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In the letter, she sincerely thanked the union for the golden autumn grant she received from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and his mother was included in the file of employees in difficulties. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the file establishment policy.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been lifted out of poverty through institutional guarantees and precise assistance.
The successful relief of Lu Ling's family and Li Yi is a microcosm of the work of Yunnan Trade Union to promote the relief of needy employees.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Work Department of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial general manager strengthened the dynamic management of the files of employees in difficulties, promoted the normalization of file-building work, and promptly incorporated into the assistance system for employees in difficulties who meet the requirements for file-building; broadened the application channels for employees in difficulties, and used WeChat to open an online file-building service platform for employees with difficulties, so as to facilitate employees in difficulties to file in a timely manner.
During the epidemic, it was difficult to go out to work. In order to help employees in difficulties alleviate the pressure of life, Yunnan Province has arranged a total of more than 13 million yuan to send warm funds. According to the national level of 2,000 yuan per household for employees in difficulties and the provincial level of 1,500 yuan per household for employees in difficulties, more than 6,000 national-level and more than 1,000 provincial-level employees in difficulties have implemented special warm condolences activities.
At the same time, the provincial general manager docked with various Internet recruitment platforms such as the Human Resources Department and Zhilian Recruitment to push recruitment information to employees in difficulties, and provide employment consulting, employment guidance and other services.
